juli 31, 2020

Load, display and clean data

d <- read.delim("geotracking_master_July16_1pm.csv", 
                   sep = ",", header = T)


qq <- read.delim("COVID-19 US state policy database (CUSP) - Reopening.tsv.txt")
tmp <- NULL; tmp$state_fips <- qq$State.FIPS.Code
tmp$reopen_barber <- qq$Reopened.hair.salons.barber.shops
tmp$reopen_religious <- qq$Reopen.Religious.gatherings

d <-
  merge(d, tmp, by = "state_fips")

# only look at data when unacast controlled for previous movement
# only use counties with population greater than 2000
d <- 
  subset(d, covid == "POST" & county_population > 2000)

# tidy up date/time object
d$date_format <-
  as.Date(d$date, format = "%m/%d/%y")

# county level GOP advantage
d$percent_dem_2016 <- 
  d$dem_2016 / d$total_2016
d$percent_gop_2016 <-
  d$gop_2016 / d$total_2016
d$gop_advantage_2016 <-
  d$percent_gop_2016 - d$percent_dem_2016

hist(d$gop_advantage_2016,
     breaks = 101)

Time variables

# create weekend dummy variable
d$weekend <- 
  ifelse(d$weekday==1 | d$weekday == 7, 1, 0)

# time variable, days since first measurment
start_day <- min(d$date_format)
d$time_day <- d$date_format - start_day

# create orthogonal time terms (up to cubic if we would need it)
table(d$time_day)  # same number of observations of each time. this is nice.

idx <- unique(d$time_day)
t <- poly(idx, 3)
d$time_day_linear <- rep(t[,1], 3025)
d$time_day_quad <- rep(t[,2], 3025)
d$time_day_cubic <- rep(t[,3], 3025)

State policy

#State policy
d$stay_at_home_enact_format <- 
  as.Date(d$StayAtHomeEnacted,format = "%m/%d/%y")
d$stay_at_home_end_format <- 
  as.Date(d$StayAtHomeEnded,format = "%m/%d/%y")

d$state_policy <- 
  ifelse(is.na(d$stay_at_home_enact_format), "no_order",
         ifelse(is.na(d$stay_at_home_end_format) & 
                  (d$date_format>=d$stay_at_home_enact_format), "stay_at_home",
                ifelse( (d$date_format>=d$stay_at_home_enact_format) & 
                          (d$date_format<d$stay_at_home_end_format), "stay_at_home", "no_order" )))

d$state_policy_dummy <-
  ifelse(d$state_policy=="stay_at_home", 1,0)
d$state_policy_c <- 
  scale(d$state_policy_dummy, scale = F)

# aggregate data
agg <- 
  with(d, 
       aggregate(
         cbind(daily_distance_diff, gop_advantage_2016, county_population),
         list(state_name, county_fips),
         mean
       )
  )

death <-
  with(d,
       aggregate(
         deaths_final, 
         list(state_name, county_fips),
         sum
       ))

agg$total_deaths_capita <- 
  death$x / agg$county_population

agg$total_deaths <- death$x
agg$total_deaths_log <- log(agg$total_deaths+1) #+1  to avoid inf
agg$gop_advantage_2016_abs <- abs(agg$gop_advantage_2016)
agg <- agg[complete.cases(agg),]

d_temp <-
  d[, c("state_name", "county_fips", "time_day", 
        "county_population", "gop_advantage_2016", 
        "daily_distance_diff")]
d_temp <- d_temp[complete.cases(d_temp),]
d_temp$gop_advantage_2016_abs <- abs(d_temp$gop_advantage_2016)

#pdf("distance_politics_time_scatter.pdf", width = 10, height = 8)
par(mfrow=c(8,7), mar = c(2.5,4,1,0), oma = rep(2,4))
for (ss in unique(d_temp$state_name)){
  my_custom_scatter(plot_dat = subset(d_temp, state_name==ss), 
                 x_var = "time_day",
                 y_var = "daily_distance_diff",
                 circle_width = "gop_advantage_2016_abs",
                 take_log_circle = F,
                 cex_scale = 0.2,
                loess_grouped = "gop_advantage_2016",
                 x_lim = c(0,82),
                 x_at = c(-0, 30, 60, 82),
                 y_lim = c(-.30, .80))
}
mtext("Physical distancing: % Reduction in Overall Movement", 2, outer = T, font = 2)
mtext("Time (days)", 1, outer = T, font = 2)
